					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm working on a project, where I have vertical mirroring in place, and have a working irq split, where the top part is stationary for text, while the bottom part (the irq) contains gfx. <br /><br />My stationary top portion resides in $2000ppu $2400ppu, while my irq split gfx are located in $2400ppu &amp; $2C00ppu.<br /><br />I'm having difficulty with my ability to select a nametable from either the stationary part of my screen, or from my irq split.<br /><br />I tried adding LDA $2002, LDA $#01(load up $2400 nametable) STA $2000, but it doesn't work. I have this within my NMI. And I also tried the same routine within my irq split, but I cant select the nametable either.<br /><br />Could someone refresh my memory on how to do this correctly. I tried looking up the nesdev wiki on PPU registers, and thought I was doing this right, but I'm not obviously. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":-(" title="Sad" /><br /><br />what I'm trying to do, is have my irq split scroll from left to right, displaying gfx from one nametable to the other, then I perform vram updates to change the current nametable im having the irq scroll to. I have my irq gfx start in $2400, then I would have gfx written into $2000, so that when the scroll count enter either 00 or FF, and dec's/inc's further, that I have the option to toggle the current viewed nametable, to give the appearance of a smooth transition.<br /><br />Thanks for reading!</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

