				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">To change <s>that</s> <em>the Y</em> part of the scroll position mid-screen, you will need to do it via writes to $2006.<br /><br />$2000 and $2005 only fully update the scroll position if they're used before the first line of rendering. After that point, $2000 won't directly change the <em>Y</em> scroll, and $2005 alone will only make changes to the X scroll, not Y.<br /><br />The canonical way to split scroll is with a set of four writes to $2006, $2005, $2005, $2006 in that order. This wiki article will explain: <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/The_skinny_on_NES_scrolling" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/The_skinny_on_NES_scrolling</a><br /><br />Alternatively, if you can live with a 1-pixel offset you could just write 255 to $2005 for the split.<br /><br /><em>Edit: fixing incorrect information, changes in italics / strikethrough.</em></div>

					
							<br /><br />
