						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">To change that part of the scroll position mid-screen, you will need to do it via writes to $2006.</div><br />Only if you need to change the vertical scroll, right?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">$2000 and $2005 only fully update the scroll position if they're used before the first line of rendering. After that point, $2000 won't directly change the scroll, and $2005 alone will only make changes to the X scroll, not Y.</div><br />AFAIK, the horizontal part of $2000 (bit 0) will be honored for the next scanline just fine.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">The canonical way to split scroll is with a set of four writes to $2006, $2005, $2005, $2006 in that order. This wiki article will explain: <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/The_skinny_on_NES_scrolling" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/The_skinny_on_NES_scrolling</a></div><br />Yes, if you have to change the vertical scroll. If you're changing only the horizontal scroll, $2000 and $2005 will work fine. According to &quot;The skinny on NES scrolling&quot;, the coarse X scrolling, along with the horizontal name table bit, is copied from &quot;t&quot; to &quot;v&quot; at the end of every scanline.</div>

