					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">idk if im not understanding, but from what im reading it looks like you guys are talking about how to peform a scrolling background. My irq I'm able to scroll freely with no issues, as well as my main stationary background.<br /><br />The irq itself is not the issue, the issue im having, is I cannot change the nametable on-the-fly for either my stationary background, or, my irq split. <br /><br />I apologize if I overlooked something with all of the replies here, its just that I saw no mention of &quot;nametable&quot; which is my big issue, since I cant change it on the fly. Thanks for reading and for your help guys!<br /><br />Here is my NMI. Idk if im missing something, or if something should have been set within my reset vector, but heres my code.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">SEI<br />PHP<br />PHA<br />TXA<br />PHA<br />TYA<br />PHA<br />LDA #$80&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ;mmc5 irq activate value<br />STA $5204&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;;mmc5 irq activated<br />LDA #$1E&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ;value for ppu rendering to turn on<br />STA $2001&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;;store 1E for ppu rendering on<br />LDA #$67&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ;irq split y position<br />STA $5203&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;;activate mmc5 irq split screen<br />LDA $2002<br />LDA $FD<br />STA $2005<br />LDA $FC<br />STA $2005<br />LDA $FF&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ;set as 00<br />STA $2000<br />PLA<br />TAY<br />PLA<br />TAX<br />PLA<br />PLP<br />RTI<br /></div><br /><br /><br /><strong>EDIT</strong><br /><br />OK there was an error on my part in my reset vector. idk where I got this from, (looking at ollllld notes of mine) but for me to initiate the NMI, it says I need to have at the end of my reset vector LDA #$80 STA $2000, then have a JMP to the LDA #$80. With that, my NMI fires up. So obviously I'm having a forced constant write to $2000 of the $2000ppu nametable.<br /><br />So, what I did was...<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">LDA #$80<br />STA $2000<br />STA $FF<br /><br />LDA $FF<br />STA $2000<br />CLI<br />JMP back to LDA $FF</div><br /><br />again to those that don't know me, that remark I made after the jmp is wrong, I don't use assemblers, I code entirely in hex. This is just to show my work to those that want it written out only, not in hex.<br /><br />So now I have full control of altering the current nametable, ONLY for my stationary background.<br /><br />I still can't cycle on-the-fly through the current viewed nametable for my irq split on the bottom of the screen...<br /><br />So what should i have within my IRQ to have free control of what nametable is viewable within the irq split? Thanks again! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /></div>

